<div class="header-section-childcare">
<h2>Licensing Options</h2>
</div>
<div class="grid-container">
<a href="https://www.ctoec.org/licensing/centers-group-child-care-homes" class="childcare-link">
<div class="board-box">
<h3>Child Care Centers</h3>
<p>Provide a program of supplementary care to more the 12 related or unrelated children outside their own home on a regular basis”. Child Care Centers are classified under 2 separate Use Groups in the  International Building Code.  Groups E  Educational and Group I Institutional. </p>
<span class="box-arrow">→</span>
</div>
</a>
<a href="https://www.ctoec.org/licensing/centers-group-child-care-homes" class="childcare-link">
<div class="board-box">
<h3>Group Child Care Homes</h3>
<p>Offers or provides  a program of supplementary care (A) to  not less than 7 or more than 12 related or unrelated children on a regular basis or, (B) that meets the definition of a family child care home except that it  operates In a facility other than a private family home.</p>
<span class="box-arrow">→</span>
</div>
</a>
<a href="https://www.ctoec.org/licensing/family-child-care-homes" class="childcare-link">
<div class="board-box">
<h3>Family Child Care Homes</h3>
<p>Consists of a private home providing care (A) for not more the 6 children, including  the provider’s own children not in school full time, without the presence or assistance of an assistant or substitute staff member approved by the commissioner of Early Childhood or not more than 9 children, including the provider’s own children, with the presence and assistance of such approved assistant or substitute staff member, and (B) for not less than 3 or more than 12 hours during a 24 period. During the regular school year and summer months 3 additional school  children are permitted.</p>
<span class="box-arrow">→</span>
</div>
</a>
</div>
